programmes.show_description: Ghosts In The Canal. Josh wants to investigate ghostly sightings and terrifying sounds coming from an abandoned canal along the Potomac. What will they uncover? S2, Ep13
Terror In Appalachia. Phil and Jess venture into the Great Smoky Mountains to investigate missing hiker reports and sightings of grotesque human-like creatures. S3, Ep1

Toronto. The buyers bid against one another for lost airport items in Toronto. Mark and Billy bid for photography equipment and the Martins want a rare stamp collection. S1, Ep11
North Carolina. The buyers are in North Carolina to bid on lost, damaged and misplaced freight. They all compete for a box of war antiques, plus they bid on a cage of unknown items. S1, Ep12
Bust A Move. The Kellys must find gold to pay off their debts. Shawn moves his camp in search of the motherlode, and Vernon's diver tries to mine without a light. S10, Ep25
Hustle And Overflow. Shawn is driven to desperate measures to solve his water overflow problems. Meanwhile, Vernon follows the gold trail despite dangerous ice conditions. S10, Ep26
The Heli Hunters go for a remote camping trip in the Murchison region of Western Australia. Near Gwalia, rookie team the Brumbies, can't seem to catch a break. S9, Ep6
Return Of The Outback Beast. Jeremy heads to Australia to investigate an underwater attack. Could it be the work of a giant fresh water predator that many believed to be extinct? S1, Ep7
Stay Focused Or Die. The typhoon has sunk one of the boats. But as the weather clears the fleet can't dwell on the tragedy and heads back out on the treacherous seas. S5, Ep3
Put Up or Shut Up. It's the 2008 King Crab season in Dutch Harbour, so get prepared for more high drama on the treacherous and deadly Bering Sea. S5, Ep4
Dragon's Teeth. Darrell focuses on a multi-million-dollar wreck tied to Sir Francis Drake. He and his team race to locate a treacherous area identified on the map as Dragon's Teeth. S2, Ep5
The Real Robin Hood. Josh Gates journeys across England to uncover the true story behind Robin Hood. He explores underground tunnels and finds what may be his final resting place. S2, Ep2
England's Vanished Crown Jewels. Josh is on a quest to find the legendary lost treasure of King John. He explores the marshlands of England to find the despised king's crown jewels. S3, Ep13
Nevada Thirst. The Kondors' homestead turns to dust and Marty gambles everything to save it. The Raney's discover infested trailers, searing heat and sand storms. S1, Ep5
Bearanoia. The Raney's are called to a failing Homestead in Colorado. Plus, Don makes a 40 mile commute each day leaving Lorinda alone and terrified of the bears and mountain lions. S1, Ep6
Aerial Opal Spotting. The mining season is almost over and Col's crew take one last gamble. The Cooke brothers strive to save their mega opal machine and disastrous season. S1, Ep8
Rookie Mistakes. With Dan stuck at home, Justin starts the new mining season alone. He is dealt a huge blow when their rich underground mine has been pegged by another miner. S2, Ep1
5-Year Storm Part 1. A menacing storm moves into the fleet, with a rogue wave ripping steel at the Cape Caution. Jake, a freshman skipper, struggles to battle through the winds. S11, Ep12
5-Year Storm Part 2. A 600-mile-wide arctic storm continues to ravage the fleet, and rookie skippers Jake Anderson and Josh Harris struggle just to keep their heads above water. S11, Ep13
A Tiger Ate My Face. Hashmot Ali had his face torn away by a tiger, and Yulianna Yussef is covered with hundreds of hairy birthmarks. Can doctors effectively treat them? S5, Ep1
Ants In My Head. An Indian girl suffers from an infestation of ants in her ear canal. And, a Brazilian woman's tiny facial birthmark has become a huge tumour despite 19 surgeries. S5, Ep2
A game changing piece of equipment leads the Ferals to their biggest nugget haul of the season. Plus, Shane and Russell battle unseasonal weather. S6, Ep11
Naked And Afraid Of Sharks. On a barren island in shark-infested waters, five all-star competitors must survive for 14 days. Can they live on only what the ocean provides? S5, Ep1

Twin Capes Ferry. The crew heads to Norfolk, Virginia, to test their sea legs and salvage a ferry including lights, skylights and a mural. Grayson helps Mike and Tay with a build. S9, Ep4
Return To The Ferry. The team returns to the Norfolk ferry to get the large items that were left behind, including a crow's nest and staircase. Mike and Robert have a consultation. S9, Ep5
Texas Cold 'Em. Shawn turns to an unusual method to track down a tricky paystreak. Vernon races against weakening ice on Claim 56. Zeke makes a late move to Tomcod. S10, Ep27
Yo Brother, Where Art Thou? With Kris away, Andy is under pressure to bring in gold as captain of the Reaper. Zeke tries Shawn's coordinates to finally get on the gold trail. S10, Ep28
Alan and Salty venture deep into Western Australia's Pilbara region. The Gold Devils struggling to find a reliable source of gold on their Fairlady lease. S9, Ep7
South Africa's Legendary Beast. A recent sighting of a local and bizarre beast, a kaaiman, calls Jeremy to South Africa. He hopes to uncover the facts behind this ancient myth. S1, Ep8
Long Haul, Short Fuses. After 40 hard days at sea the pressure is on and tempers boil over on deck. And the superstitious Captain Keith is upset to have missed a herd of walruses. S5, Ep5
Deadline. A new deadline is set - an upcoming drop in the price of king crab has the skippers rushing to finish their season. But crew battles and a fierce arctic storm block the way. S5, Ep6
Island Of Fortune. Darrell and the team head to a mysterious island where they discover valuable clues that lead them closer in the hunt to a 500-year-old shipwreck. S2, Ep6
The Warrior Queen's Treasure. Josh Gates searches across England to unearth a cache of ancient treasures belonging to the legendary Celtic queen, Boudica. S6, Ep16
The Quest For King Arthur. Josh Gates traverses England, Wales and Scotland, wading through history and legend to search for evidence of a real King Arthur. S2, Ep1
Wolves At The Door. The Raneys help the Johnson family who have no drinking water or food sources. Their dogs have been killed by a mystery predator and worry they are next. S1, Ep7
Trapped. The Raneys assist two Montana homesteaders who face being trapped on their property. When a medical emergency strikes, the Raneys face their first ever failed rescue. S1, Ep8
Wild Wild West. Justin's excavator has an expensive oil leak. Plus, Col's crew are a man down and the Fire Crew are on a wild goose chase hunting a bounty of fabled fire opal. S2, Ep2
Going Under. For the Rookies, there's tension as a new partner leads them on a wild goose chase underground. Plus, the Cooke Brothers' season is off to a bad and dangerous start. S2, Ep3
Bite the Hand. A second major storm hits the fleet. While rookie skipper Jake Anderson reaches out to Sig Hansen for help, Josh Harris arrives on the grounds weeks late. S11, Ep14
New Blood, Old Wounds. Late into Opilio season, the fleet battles against mental & physical breakdown. After deliberately defying Sig, Captain Jake Anderson has a shot at redemption. S11, Ep15
Deep Mud, Deeper State. When state inspectors make a surprise visit to the mine, the Hoffman team races to save their operation before the inspectors return with a verdict. S2, Ep6
The Purpose Of Porpoises. For the first time, Captain Sig faces a man overboard. The tide turns for Johnathan when thousands of porpoises guide the Time Bandit to new grounds. S20, Ep6
The Poseidon Crew are slowed down by fierce storms. Jacqui and Andrew encounter a deadly insect, while the Gold Timers try to fix their dry blower. S6, Ep12
